creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of The National Geographic Magazine Vol. 07 - 04. April 1896 by Various.
Read in English by Ky; BettyB; MaryAnnS; Availle; Rapunzelina; A514E
The National Geographic Magazine, an illustrated monthly, the April Number.
It includes the following articles:
  • Serilan, by by W J McGee and Willard D. Johnson
  • The Olympic Country, by S. C. Gilman, C. E.
  • The Discovery of Glacier Bay, Alaska, by Eliza Ruhamah Scidmore
  • Hydrography in the United States, by Frederick H. Newell
  • Recent Triangulation in the Cascades, by S. S. Gannett
  • The Altitude of Mount Adams, Washington, by Edgar McClure
along with geographic literature and a few miscellanea notes.

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
